
                                            Wilfred Oliphant admitted to killing the mother and her child in June 2017.
                                         CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape High Court has sentenced an Atlantis man to 20 years behind bars for the murder of a 22-year-old woman and her two-year-old daughter. Wilfred Oliphant admitted to killing the mother and her child in June 2017.  Police arrested the 35-year-old shortly after the victims’ bodies were found.  Oliphant received 15 years behind bars for the murder of Octavia Skippers and another 15 years imprisonment for taking the life of the woman’s toddler, Cleo.  The Western Cape High Court has ordered that 10 years run concurrently.  In his plea, Oliphant admitted to assaulting both victims and burying their heads in the sand in a bushy area in Witsand.  He also admitted to being high on drugs at the time of the attack.  Skippers and her daughter were last seen by their family as they left to go to the hairdresser.  Oliphant is known to the family. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)